    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <head>258. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3"
                        type="to">Rusk</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d258fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 770B.5-MSP/7-561. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-07-05">July 5, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to your memorandum of July 1, 1961 concerning the latest
                    developments with regard to our Guinea Aid Program<note n="1" xml:id="d258fn1">
                        <ref target="#d257">Document 257</ref>.</note> is there any chance that we
                    could finance the big dam in Guinea if we omitted all the other elements of our
                    aid program? How much would we pay off dollar wise to be able to do this?</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
